y of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from one of the many places (most notably one in Lancashire) so called from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","occasionally from Middle English <i>prest</i> + <i>son</i> ‘son of the priest’. Priests were forbidden marriage but many produced illegitimate offspring."],"variants":[{"name":"Presson","meanings":["English (Cheshire and Lancashire): variant of   Preston  .","French: occupational name for a presser of wine or oil, from a derivative of <i>presser</i> ‘to press’."]},{"name":"Prestwich","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from a place in Lancashire (now Greater Manchester), so called from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘outlying settlement’, or from other places with the same derivation. Variants such as <i>Prestidge</i>, <i>Prestage</i>, etc., parallel the local pronunciation of the Lancashire name. Compare   Preston  ."]}]},{"name":"Esther","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by a Jewish captive who became the wife of the Persian king Ahasuerus. Her Hebrew name was <i>Hadassah</i> ‘myrtle’, and the form <i>Esther</i> is said to be a Persian translation of this, although others derive it from Persian <i>stara</i> ‘star’. It may also be a Hebrew form of the name of the Persian goddess <i>Ishtar</i>. According to the book of the Bible that bears her name, Esther managed, by her perception and persuasion, to save large numbers of the Jews from the evil machinations of the royal counsellor Haman.  See also  Hester ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":20,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":33,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":42,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Esther Preston was born in 1295, in Buckinghamshire, England as the daughter of James Preston and Letitia. She had at least 1 son with Fulco Ballard."},"et":{"1295–":"1295–Surnud","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","1250–1346":"1250–1346","1330–1382":"1330–1382","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1346":"1346","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1250":"1250","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1260":"1260","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1295–":"1295–Kuollut","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","1250–1346":"1250–1346","1330–1382":"1330–1382","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1346":"1346","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1250":"1250","about 1330":"noin 1330","1260":"1260","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1295–":"1295–Décédée","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","1250–1346":"1250–1346","1330–1382":"1330–1382","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","